9 December 2011 The South African government delegation will brief media on matters related to the United Nations Framework on Climate Change (UNFCCC) Conference of Parties (COP17/CMP7) being held in Durban, South Africa.The Ministers in attendance will include the Minister of State Security, Mr Siyabonga Cwele and the Minister of Home Affairs, Ms Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma.Details of the briefing are as follows:Date: Friday, 9 December 2011 Time: 15h00 Venue: Yellowwood, on Level 1 of the Inkosi Albert Luthuli International Convention Centre (ICC), DurbanIssued by: Government Communication and Information System (GCIS)